There is no specific regulation regarding online processing of personal data. Thus, online privacy and data processing is governed by Law 1581.
Personal data must not be available online unless there are adequate security measures to ensure that access by any unauthorized user is restricted.
Collection and use of data collected through cookies or similar online tracking tools is prohibited unless the Data Subject has provided consent. Such consent may be obtained by a pop-up informing the user about the company's privacy policy and ways for the Data Subject's to review, manage or disable cookies.Last modified 24 Jan 2022
				
			